# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:46
translate spanish hwb_s09_f3973940:

    # "Arizona’s highways are infamously boring. Nothing but hills; up, down, up, down. There’s nothing interesting to look at. Both sides of the road are smothered in nondescript shrubs."
    "Las autopistas de Arizona son famosamente aburridas. Solo colinas; arriba, abajo, arriba, abajo. No hay nada interesante que ver. Ambos lados de la carretera están cubiertos de arbustos sin nombre."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:48
translate spanish hwb_s09_5e36523b:

    # "It’s the part of the country where you just zone out and drive on autopilot."
    "Es la parte del país donde simplemente te desconectas y conduces en piloto automático."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:50
translate spanish hwb_s09_e4f2c5ab:

    # "When we finally see a sign for the town of Chinle, right next to the canyon, it feels like we’re approaching the Promised Land."
    "Cuando finalmente vemos un letrero del pueblo de Chinle, justo al lado del cañón, se siente como si nos acercáramos a la Tierra Prometida."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:52
translate spanish hwb_s09_2878df1f:

    # "Marina looks up from the book she’s reading just in time to miss the sign."
    "Marina levanta la vista del libro que está leyendo justo a tiempo para perderse el letrero."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:56
translate spanish hwb_s09_23abab81:

    # Marina "Was that it? Are we there yet?"
    Marina "Что там было написано? Мы уже приехали?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:58
translate spanish hwb_s09_103a710f:

    # Amber "Nah. Forty miles to go still. So about half an hour."
    Amber "Неа. Еще сорок миль. Так что, ехать где-то около получаса."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:62
translate spanish hwb_s09_20a80ec1:

    # "She makes a sound like a popped balloon and goes back to reading."
    "Hace un sonido como un globo desinflado y vuelve a leer."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:64
translate spanish hwb_s09_20541a11:

    # "We take an exit in a tiny excuse for a town; one of those places that has a gas station and a few old houses."
    "Tomamos una salida en un pueblecito minúsculo; de esos lugares que tienen una gasolinera y unas cuantas casas viejas."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:66
translate spanish hwb_s09_37fc76d5:

    # "It’s like in Monopoly, where you buy up all the property you can, even though it’s not that great."
    "Es como en el Monopoly, donde compras todas las propiedades que puedes, aunque no sean tan buenas."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:70
translate spanish hwb_s09_3fc488bb:

    # Marina "This is it?"
    Marina "Это оно?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:72
translate spanish hwb_s09_cafbd514:

    # "Marina repeats her earlier question as I slow down to turn left."
    "Marina repite su pregunta anterior mientras reduzco la velocidad para girar a la izquierda."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:74
translate spanish hwb_s09_2ac0dcf7:

    # Amber "Nope. Almost. I don’t even know what this place is called."
    Amber "Неа. Почти. Я даже не знаю название этого места."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:78
translate spanish hwb_s09_59845d57:

    # "She makes the popped balloon noise again, but leaves the book closed."
    "Vuelve a hacer el sonido del globo desinflado, pero deja el libro cerrado."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:80
translate spanish hwb_s09_f7048653:

    # "When we finally reach Chinle, it’s pretty obvious. This is the first real town we’ve seen in hours."
    "Cuando finalmente llegamos a Chinle, es bastante obvio. Este es el primer pueblo real que vemos en horas."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:82
translate spanish hwb_s09_42025ee0:

    # "The outskirts are industrial, dominated by what I assume are factories."
    "Las afueras son industriales, dominadas por lo que supongo que son fábricas."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:84
translate spanish hwb_s09_ea7a0d8b:

    # "A pair of stray dogs lope along the side of the road, hungry and lean. Marina makes a sound of sympathy, pressing her face against the glass as we pass them."
    "Un par de perros callejeros trotan por el costado de la carretera, hambrientos y flacos. Marina hace un sonido de compasión, presionando su rostro contra el vidrio mientras los pasamos."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:88
translate spanish hwb_s09_93cd1da8:

    # Marina "Hey Amber?"
    Marina "Эй, Эмбер?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:90
translate spanish hwb_s09_43e2dadc:

    # Amber "We’re not getting a dog."
    Amber "Мы не будем брать с собой собаку."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:94
translate spanish hwb_s09_dfa17a86:

    # Marina "But they’re so cute! And we could dress him up in a bandanna and-"
    Marina "Но они такие милые! И мы можем надеть на нее бандану и-"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:96
translate spanish hwb_s09_3320639e:

    # Amber "No way. I’ve never gotten why people wanna dress their pets up like people."
    Amber "Ни за что. Никогда не могла понять, зачем люди наряжают своих питомцев как людей."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:100
translate spanish hwb_s09_e1d6cbb5:

    # Marina "It’s cute."
    Marina "Это мило."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:102
translate spanish hwb_s09_891ff58b:

    # "Marina pouts. I figured she was just joking, but she didn’t actually think I would let her get a dog, right?"
    "Marina hace un puchero. Supuse que solo bromeaba, pero no pensó que realmente la dejaría tener un perro, ¿verdad?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:106
translate spanish hwb_s09_7624a28f:

    # "It seems that all is forgiven by the time I pull into a gas station. She’s bouncing in her seat with her usual enthusiasm. Or maybe it’s her bladder."
    "Parece que todo está perdonado para cuando llego a una gasolinera. Está saltando en su asiento con su entusiasmo habitual. O tal vez es su vejiga."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:108
translate spanish hwb_s09_714a9015:

    # "My second guess must have been correct, because as soon as I shut off the engine, she darts out of the RV and into the store."
    "Mi segunda suposición debe haber sido correcta, porque apenas apago el motor, sale disparada de la casa rodante y entra a la tienda."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:110
translate spanish hwb_s09_d4f22cd1:

    # "While she does that, I fuel up. No telling when we'll see the next gas station. Could be a hundred miles. And this thing drinks gasoline like a thirsty dog drinks water."
    "Mientras ella hace eso, yo cargo gasolina. No hay forma de saber cuándo veremos la próxima gasolinera. Podrían ser cien millas. Y esta cosa bebe gasolina como un perro sediento bebe agua."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:112
translate spanish hwb_s09_f3a65d4d:

    # "By the time I finish, Marina still isn't back, so I lock up and head inside."
    "Para cuando termino, Marina aún no ha vuelto, así que cierro con llave y entro."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:147
translate spanish hwb_s09_47bd61a2:

    # "The store is devoid of other customers. It’s unremarkable, with the usual selection of candy, chips, and overpriced beef jerky."
    "La tienda está vacía de otros clientes. Es común y corriente, con la selección habitual de dulces, papas fritas y carne seca demasiado cara."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:149
translate spanish hwb_s09_a6e3f5ca:

    # "I’m not hungry, just passing time."
    "No tengo hambre, solo paso el tiempo."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:161
translate spanish hwb_s09_910308f7:

    # "Soon, Marina trots out of the bathroom, glancing around. She spots me and heads over."
    "Pronto, Marina sale trotando del baño, mirando alrededor. Me ve y se acerca."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:163
translate spanish hwb_s09_640a62d7:

    # Amber "Want anything?"
    Amber "Что-нибудь хочешь?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:167
translate spanish hwb_s09_020ddb6e:

    # Marina "Duh. Let’s see…"
    Marina "А то. Давай-ка глянем, что тут есть…"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:186
translate spanish hwb_s09_2f515590:

    # "I leave her to agonize over the candy bars while I flip through some of the travel brochures beneath the window. There are a couple about Canyon de Chelly, which is our destination just up the road."
    "La dejo angustiarse por las barras de chocolate mientras hojeo algunos de los folletos de viaje debajo de la ventana. Hay un par sobre Canyon de Chelly, que es nuestro destino justo al final del camino."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:188
translate spanish hwb_s09_8276883e:

    # "There are flyers for other Arizona attractions, too, including the non-local ones. Of course there are a few brochures for the Grand Canyon, plus a couple “must-see” sights in Phoenix, the capital."
    "También hay volantes para otras atracciones de Arizona, incluyendo las que no son locales. Por supuesto, hay algunos folletos para el Gran Cañón, además de un par de lugares \"imperdibles\" en Phoenix, la capital."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:190
translate spanish hwb_s09_7a7113fd:

    # "There’s even an ad for a novelty just called “The Thing” in Tucson, but that’s far out of our way."
    "Incluso hay un anuncio de una novedad llamada \"La Cosa\" en Tucson, pero eso está muy fuera de nuestro camino."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:198
translate spanish hwb_s09_be8e96b8:

    # Marina "Okay, I’m ready."
    Marina "Ну все, я готова."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:200
translate spanish hwb_s09_e6ebaadf:

    # "I turn around. Marina has a couple king-sized candy bars in her hands, and a large bottle of Coke tucked under her arm."
    "Me doy la vuelta. Marina tiene un par de barras de chocolate tamaño gigante en las manos y una botella grande de Coca-Cola bajo el brazo."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:204
translate spanish hwb_s09_6f3338d4:

    # Amber "You seriously need all that?"
    Amber "Тебе правда все это нужно?"

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:208
translate spanish hwb_s09_447ca05b:

    # Marina "I thought we could share."
    Marina "Я думала поделиться."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:210
translate spanish hwb_s09_9a7b4302:

    # "She gives me her best “offended puppy” impression."
    "Me da su mejor impresión de \"cachorro ofendido\"."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:214
translate spanish hwb_s09_b4dc184c:

    # Amber "Fine, fine."
    Amber "Ладно, ладно."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:216
translate spanish hwb_s09_c939e80c:

    # "I still don’t want anything, but I can’t say no to that."
    "Sigo sin querer nada, pero no puedo decirle que no a eso."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:220
translate spanish hwb_s09_9f46cdd2:

    # Amber "Here, I’m gonna use the bathroom too. Meet you at the car."
    Amber "Подожди, я тоже схожу в уборную. Встретимся у машины."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:227
translate spanish hwb_s09_c9036b6b:

    # "I place my wallet atop the pallet of candy she’s carrying and send her towards the attendant."
    "Coloco mi cartera encima del montón de dulces que lleva y la envío hacia el dependiente."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:235
translate spanish hwb_s09_f5dafc81:

    # "When I come back out of the bathroom, Marina’s still talking to the clerk. There’s a bag in her hands, so she must have already finished paying and gotten distracted talking."
    "Cuando salgo del baño, Marina todavía está hablando con el empleado. Tiene una bolsa en las manos, así que ya debe haber terminado de pagar y se distrajo hablando."

# game/script/hwb_s09.rpy:242
translate spanish hwb_s09_9fc50a2b:

    # "I join the two of them."
    "Me uno a ellos."


## NEED THIS but ahhh it clashes with credits TL
